            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-02-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-02-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="98" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d98">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">121.893/2–2546: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Marshall</persName> to President
                            <persName type="to">Truman</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-02-24">24 February
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>[244.] <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. President</hi>: The Generalissimo returned
                    from a 10-day trip this afternoon, Sunday, stopping at his country place. He
                    asks me to motor down to talk to him and dine with him tomorrow.</p>
                <p>Meanwhile, I am informed that he has approved our agreement for demobilization,
                    reorganization, and integration of the Chinese armies. The meeting to sign the
                    agreement by my committee is set for 4:00 PM tomorrow. A complete press release
                    will probably follow shortly, I suppose.</p>
                <p>Executive Headquarters in Peiping is charged with the execution of the agreement.
                    I will radio full details later.</p>
                <p>Faithfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>G. C. <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
